<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-041-624  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 041 624.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Jan 11 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Chicago schools order Wicat Systems for learning centers.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Goldie, Beth; McCormick, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Wicat Systems Inc. (contracts).andO;Ticker:    WCAT.andO;Topic:     Computer industryChicago. Public SchoolsContractsMicrocomputersComputer-Assisted Instruction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>CHICAGO SCHOOLS ORDER WICAT SYSTEMS FOR LEARNING CENTERS CHICAGO, ILLINOIS,U.S.A., 1990 JAN 8 (NB) -- The Chicago Public School System and Orem,Utah-based Wicat Systems Inc. have announced agreements on contractstotalling approximately $1.1 million, to add 10 computer-based integratedlearning centers in eight inner-city schools.andM;These new centers, bringing the total number in the city to 27, in 18schools, will be used mostly as an adjunct to the Chapter I education programwhich helps underprivileged children.andM;The Chicago Public School System has one of the better computer- aidedteaching programs in the U.S.andP;  This specific Wicat computer- aided teachingmethod helps with the diagnosis and treatment of learning problems, anecessary procedure now that the need for better education is beingemphasized nationwide.andM;(Beth Goldie and John McCormick/1990109/Press Contact: Sally Jenkins, WicatSystems Inc., 801-224-6400, ext. 304)</TEXT></DOC>